constructor.details: Initializes the proxy by delegating a call to the `initialize` function of the implementation provided by the token factory.

params.accessManager_: The access manager of the bond.
params.decimals_: The number of decimals of the bond.
params.faceValue_: The face value of the bond.
params.identityRegistry_: The identity registry of the bond.
params.initialModulePairs_: The initial module pairs of the bond.
params.maturityDate_: The maturity date of the bond.
params.onchainID_: Optional address of an existing onchain identity contract. Pass address(0) to create a new
params.tokenFactoryAddress: The address of the token factory contract.
params.underlyingAsset_: The underlying asset of the bond.

ETHTransfersNotAllowed().notice: Error indicating that an attempt was made to send Ether to a contract that does not allow or expect it.

InitializationWithZeroAddress().notice: Error indicating that an attempt was made to initialize a component with a zero address for its implementation.

InvalidTokenFactoryAddress().notice: Error indicating that an invalid token factory address was provided.

TokenImplementationNotSet().notice: Error indicating that the token implementation address has not been set.

userdoc.notice: This contract serves as a proxy, allowing for upgradeability of the underlying bond logic. It retrieves the implementation address from the ISMARTTokenFactory contract via ATKAssetProxy.

constructor.details: Initializes the proxy by delegating a call to the `initialize` function of the implementation provided by the token factory.

params.accessManager_: The access manager of the bond.
params.decimals_: The number of decimals of the bond.

params.identityRegistry_: The identity registry of the bond.

params.maturityDate_: The maturity date of the bond.

ETHTransfersNotAllowed().details: Many contracts are not designed to receive or hold Ether directly, and will revert such transactions to prevent loss of funds or unexpected behavior.

InitializationWithZeroAddress().details: This typically occurs in proxy constructors if the logic contract address fetched from the system is address(0).
